div.div:
NodeJS projects (eg. Inbox contract)
sol contracts
local testing: MOCHA + Ganache (test network)
deployment
CONTRACT - compile and export .sol contract file
npm install solc
compile - js needs to read .sol file using fs and path modules and readFileSync
NOTE: compiler can compile multiple contracts at a time
const solc = require('solc')
we need from compiled contract the "bytecode" and "interface" (ABI)
export contract prop: module.exports = solc.compile(source,1).contracts[':Inbox'];TESTING
using Ganache (aka TestRPC) test network
npm install --save mocha ganache-cli web3
use web3 to get access to ganache accounts web3.eth.getAccounts()
import the compiled contract properties
const {interface, bytecode} = require('./compiledfile')
DEPLOY TO GANACHE (eg. Inbox example)
use one account from ganache to deploy contract (person deploying)
deploy...
result = await new web3.eth.Contract(JSON.parse(interface))
.deploy({data: bytecode, arguments:['helloworld']})
.send({from:accounts[0], gas:'1000000'})
result is a reference to contract
should test if deployed contract has an address, if property exists, it means deployed: assert.ok(result.options.address);
should test if you can call methods of contract: eg. setMessage
should test if there is default value if one is passed in when deployed
DEPLOYMENT TO INFURIA
npm install @truffle/hdwallet-provider
HDWalletProvider = require('@truffle/hdwallet-provider');
const provider = new HDWalletProvider(Mnemonic, INFURIA url of network to connect)
web3 = new Web3(provider);
use deploy script where its deployed to is result.options.address
